One operating system function is to provide a user interface. 
That controls how data and instructions are entered and displayed on the screen.
This may be through the GUI or the command-line.

Another function is starting your computer or mobile device.
This runs a teston all the devices and begins the boot up proccess from the kernel.
It then loads system configuration information and the GUI

Operating Systems also function to shut down computers. 
Pressing the power button will begin the shutdown process.
The OS will ask to save any unsaved files and power down the computer.
If you hold down the power button it goes straight to power down.
